27/03/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The court in Pozarevac began a trial in absentia Wednesday (March 26th) against the son of former Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic. 
Marko Milosevic and his mother, Mirjana, are charged in Serbia with organising of cigarette smuggling ring in the early 1990s. 
Marko is also wanted for injuring members of a resistance movement during a fight in 2000. 
Mother and son have been living for years now in Moscow and Russia refuses to extradite them, citing the refugee status they have received. 
(RIA-Novosti, News.ru, Gazeta.ru - 26/03/08)
